description:
This repository contains data used for the testing of  HTSinfer , a Python-based tool to infer metadata directly from bulk RNA-sequencing data, generated on Illumina platforms.&nbsp; 
 The repository includes the sample tables containing metadata from the 72 self-generated and publicly shared RNA-Seq samples, the 720 samples collected from the SRA database, and the aggregated tables, describing the results of the inference.&nbsp; 
 For testing purposes, HTSinfer was installed from&nbsp; Bioconda  and executed with default settings, except for the  --records  parameter, which was adjusted in the case of the 720 RNA-Seq samples set. HTSinfer was tested with the  --records  argument set to different values (10 thousand, 100 thousand, 1 million, 10 million, and 0 &ndash; indicating all records) to evaluate performance and runtimes. 
 A supplementary table comparing the functionality of HTSinfer with other available metadata inference tools is also available in the repository.

